      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): default memorySearch provider to \"auto\" instead of \"openai\"",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAfter upgrading to 2026.6.1, the `memorySearch` provider silently resets to `\"openai\"` when no provider is explicitly configured. Previously (2026.5.26) the default was `\"auto\"`, which correctly auto-selected an available embedding provider (e.g. `gemini-embedding-001` for Google AI Studio users).\n\nThe regression was introduced in commit `4d89e00c50` (\"feat(embeddings): add OpenAI-compatible core provider (#85269)\") which hardcoded the unresolved default to `\"openai\"` (`DEFAULT_MEMORY_EMBEDDING_PROVIDER`), bypassing the auto-select mechanism.\n\nFixes #90787\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: memorySearch provider silently defaults to \"openai\" when not configured, instead of \"auto\". This breaks vector search for users without an OpenAI API key — the index identity check compares against an empty string and permanently pauses vector search.\n\n**Real setup tested**: Node v24.13.1 running on Linux x86_64, on a local worktree branch of openclaw/openclaw@main (commit bf872b30cd). Verifying the mergeConfig default value fix that restores \"auto\" as the default memorySearch provider.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/memory-search.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\nTerminal capture of the actual test run:\n\n```\n> node scripts/test-projects.mjs \"src/agents/memory-search.test.ts\"\n\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n   Start at  23:28:38\n   Duration  6.22s (transform 2.82s, setup 0ms, import 5.37s, tests 500ms, environment 0ms)\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 16.33s\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: All 35 tests pass. The key behavioral changes verified by the updated test expectations:\n\n- `defaults provider to auto when unspecified` — unconfigured provider now resolves to `\"auto\"` instead of `\"openai\"`\n- `preserves explicit auto provider config` — explicitly setting `\"auto\"` is preserved through config resolution\n- All existing explicit provider tests remain passing: `\"openai\"`, `\"local\"`, `\"none\"`, and custom provider aliases all resolve identically to pre-fix behavior\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end verification with live embedding providers (Google AI Studio, OpenAI) was not performed — that would require live API keys and a running OpenClaw gateway. The fix is validated at the config-resolution unit test level (`memory-search.test.ts`), which is the exact layer where the regression was introduced and where the default provider value is resolved.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n| Test Type | Result | Details |\n|-----------|--------|---------|\n| Unit Tests | ✅ | 35/35 passed |\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**Yes** — users who did not configure `memorySearch.provider` will now get `\"auto\"` behavior (auto-select available provider) instead of being forced to `\"openai\"`. This restores the 2026.5.26 behavior. Users who explicitly configured a provider are unaffected.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No** — only the unconfigured default value changed; all explicit configurations are preserved identically.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes` / `No`)\n\n**No** — this is a config-layer default value change only.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n- Users who explicitly set `provider: \"openai\"` are unaffected.\n- Users who explicitly set `provider: \"auto\"` are unaffected (the value is now preserved through the config layer instead of being resolved at config time).\n- The only behavioral change is for users with no `provider` setting — they regain auto-select functionality.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n- All existing unit tests pass, including explicit provider configuration tests.\n- The change is a one-line default value restoration.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n- Maintainer review",
        "branch": "fix/issue-90787-memorysearch-provider-silently-resets-to-openai-after-upgrade",
